i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roku-cypher-002233723.html">originals</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roku-channel-tribeca-film-festival-channel-172006958.html">live TV</a> . Now, it has a chance to attract sports fans.</p><p> There&#39;s plenty of pressure to grow. Numerous other streaming services have their own sports exclusives. Amazon Prime Video streams a limited number of <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-prime-video-nfl-black-friday-game-date-211050980.html">NFL games</a> , while Apple has Friday Night Baseball and MLS Season Pass. Paramount+ already has <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/paramount-plus-uefa-champions-league-streaming-rights-soccer-152206370.html">multiple soccer exclusives</a> . Moreover, ad-supported channels are reaching more platforms — Amazon recently launched its own <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-rolls-out-free-roku-like-tv-channels-for-fire-devices-230056933.html">free TV for Fire devices</a> . Formula E could sustain interest in Roku&#39;s hardware and services, especially for viewers who crave live content.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/roku-will-stream-live-formula-e-races-for-free-145612443.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/roku-will-stream-live-formula-e-races-for-free-145612443.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c3455907-aea5-43b3-a097-15fb9c98d931</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Tue, 27 Jun 2023 14:56:12 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687877773</ingested><modified> 2023-06-27T14:56:16+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Motor Racing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Formula One]]></category><category><![CDATA[Sports & Recreation]]></category><category><![